### 3.2 V2 Model Architecture: Multi-Modal TFT

The core shift from V1 (LSTM) to V2 is the **Temporal Fusion Transformer**, which provides:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│          TEMPORAL FUSION TRANSFORMER (TFT)           │
│                                                       │
│  ┌─────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────┐  │
│  │  Static Inputs  │   │   Dynamic Time-Varying   │  │
│  │  (per ticker)   │   │       Inputs             │  │
│  │  • Sector       │   │  UNKNOWN (not known up   │  │
│  │  • log_market_  │   │  front): OHLCV, RSI,     │  │
│  │    cap          │   │  MACD, ATR, VIX, OBV,    │  │
│  │  • Beta         │   │  Stochastic, Lags…       │  │
│  └────────┬────────┘   │  KNOWN_FUTURE: DOW,      │  │
│           │            │  Month, Quarter, Earnings │  │
│           │            └────────────┬────────────-┘  │
│           └───────────┬─────────────┘                │
│                       ▼                              │
│           ┌──────────────────────┐                  │
│           │ Variable Selection   │ ← Ignores noisy  │
│           │ Network (VSN)        │   features auto  │
│           └──────────┬───────────┘                  │
│                      ▼                              │
│           ┌──────────────────────┐                  │
│           │ Multi-Head Self-     │ ← Detects long-  │
│           │ Attention            │   term patterns  │
│           └──────────┬───────────┘                  │
│                      ▼                              │
│           ┌──────────────────────┐                  │
│           │ Quantile Output      │ P10 / P50 / P90  │
│           └──────────────────────┘                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Keras Ensemble Model ([CausalTradingEngine](file:///d:/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/utils/model.py#115-262) — [utils/model.py](file:///d:/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/utils/model.py))**

In parallel to TFT, the platform also runs a 3-model ensemble for direction + magnitude:

| Sub-Model | Architecture | Weight | Output |
|-----------|-------------|--------|--------|
| GRU Direction | GRU(64) → Multi-Head Attention (4 heads) → GRU(32) → Sigmoid | 40% | Direction probability |
| TCN Direction | Causal Conv1D (dilation 1,2,4) → MHA → Flatten → Dense | 40% | Direction probability |
| LightGBM Direction | Gradient Boosted Trees on flattened sequences | 20% | Direction probability |
| Magnitude Model | GRU(64) → MHA → GRU(32) → Dense(3) | — | Q10/Q50/Q90 returns |

> **Causal Padding** is enforced in all CNN layers to prevent data leakage. **RobustScaler** handles outliers.

