## 6. Signal Gatekeeping System ([signal_gate.py](file:///d:/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/signal_gate.py))

Before a signal reaches a user, it must pass **3 independent gates**. All must pass for a non-HOLD signal:

| Gate | Condition | Threshold | Fail → |
|------|-----------|-----------|--------|
| **Gate 1** | TFT attention score (model confidence) | ≥ **0.65** | HOLD |
| **Gate 2** | Forecast cone width [(P90–P10)/P50](file:///d:/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/screener.py#334-342) | ≤ **15%** | HOLD |
| **Gate 3** | Sentiment agreement with direction | BUY requires sentiment > −0.3; SELL requires sentiment < +0.3 | HOLD |

**[SignalOutput](file:///d:/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/signal_gate.py#71-116) dataclass** returned to the caller contains:

- `action`: `'BUY'` | `'SELL'` | `'HOLD'`
- [confidence](file:///d:/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/alerts.py#841-845): 0.0 – 1.0 (from attention weights)
- `reason`: Human-readable explanation of which gate passed or failed
- `p10`, [p50](file:///d:/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/screener.py#77-158), `p90`: Probabilistic price forecast
- `expected_return_pct`: [(P50 – current) / current × 100](file:///d:/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/AI-Stock-market-prediction-master/screener.py#334-342)
- `gate_results`: Full pass/fail dictionary for debugging

